{{end}}{{- end}}
</rules>

<agent_memory>
AGENT_NOTES.md in the package root accumulates knowledge across runs. Prior notes are pre-loaded in <agent_notes> tags in your context — treat them as institutional knowledge, but verify any factual claim before acting on it if it contradicts what you observe.

Rules for write_note:
- verified_by is mandatory — cite the exact command you ran that proves the note is correct.
- Never write that something does not exist or is from a different package without running 'go doc' first.
- Notes about idioms must cite 'go fix -diff' or 'go doc' as evidence — not a failed build.
</agent_memory>

<completion>
When the pass is complete, call finish with status "passed" and a summary of what you improved and how each change was verified. If you are genuinely stuck, call finish with status "blocked" and explain why.
</completion>
